            <!-- Job 2 -->
            <div class="exp-card mb-4">
                <h5 class="fw-semibold text-light">Graduate Assistant (RA &amp; TA)</h5>
                <p class="text-light mb-1">
                    <strong>
                        <a href="https://wvstateu.edu/" target="_blank" class="text-warning text-decoration-none">
                            West Virginia State University
                        </a>
                    </strong><br />
                    <span class="text-muted">Jan 2023 – Dec 2024</span><br />
                    <strong>
                        <a href="https://wvstateu.edu/college-of-natural-sciences-and-mathematics/departments/mathematics-and-computer-science/" target="_blank" class="text-warning text-decoration-none">
                            Department of Math &amp; Computer Science
                        </a>
                    </strong>
                </p>
                <ul class="text-light">
                    <li>Conducted research in AI/ML-driven cybersecurity at the Cybersecurity Innovation Center, focusing on detecting and defending against cyberattacks targeting critical infrastructure (e.g., phishing, ransomware, DDoS).</li>
                    <li>Designed and developed intelligent control systems for robotic prosthetic upper limbs using 1D CNNs and embedded AI for real-time signal processing.</li>
                    <li>Built predictive models for flood forecasting and groundwater level prediction using LSTM, BiLSTM, and GRU architectures.</li>
                    <li>Contributed to research on multimodal large language models and their application in security and communication.</li>
                    <li>Assisted in teaching Data Structures, Software Engineering, and Database Management; provided lecture support, grading, and one-on-one tutoring.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <!-- Job 3 -->
            <div class="exp-card mb-4">
                <h5 class="fw-semibold text-light">IT Assistant – Intern</h5>
                <p class="text-light mb-1">
